A meeting of governors from Southeast, Southwest and South south States is currently taking place in the Delta State capital, Asaba. The meeting according sources may not be unconnected with the spate of insecurity in the country. It would be recalled that new security measures were released by President Muhammadu Buhari specifically for the Southeast and South south zones.  The new Inspector General of Police had in a press briefing disclosed that the President had approved a new security measure aimed at arresting the insecurity situation in the regions. The governors of Sates in the three regions are expected to fashion out ways to address the insecurity in their respective regions. Reports monitored showed that lagos State, Ogun, Ebonyi, Enugu, Akwa Ibom among others have already arrived Asaba. Governor Ifeanyi Okowa is playing host. Details of their meeting will be released in due course. Source: Drumnewsonline Following the spate of insecurity in the country, South South governors have agreed to float a regional security outfit to mitigate the ugly trend. This was part of decisions reached at the South South governors Forum meeting held at Government House Asaba on Thursday, 5th March, 2020. Briefing the press… In "News" By Emmanuel Acha Enugu - Governors of the South East region have appealed for audience with President Muhammadu Buhari and security chiefs in the country over insecurity in the region.The Chairman, South East Governors Forum, Gov. Dave Umahi of Ebonyi, disclosed this on Saturday while briefing newsmen after the forum’s… In "News" The World Igbo Congress, WIC, has rejected South East Governors’ formation of EbubeAgu as an alternative regional security outfit. The group rather, urged the governors to support the Eastern Security Network, ESN, stop their ruse and serve the people. This came as the Indigenous People of Biafra, IPOB,raised the alarm… In "News"